headline: Procter & Gamble is portfolio manager's 'dark horse' stock pick for 2026
summary: STORY: EDITORS PLEASE NOTE: THIS HAS BEEN RESENT TO CORRECT THE SPELLING OF PROCTER & GAMBLE IN THE HEADLINE. NO CHANGES TO VIDEO.Mulberry says easing pressure on consumers could help drive demand for Procter & Gamble’s core brands."As you look at the pressures that they've been under, it's been around those issues that seem to be getting better, the currency exchange rate and also looking at more stable trading policies. If we combine that with lower overall costs in energy and housing, then we could start to see consumers come back to the name brands that they desperately want in home goods and baby care."
